      "content": "i mean, \"systemic emissions\" vs \"finite burden\" sounds a bit one-sided. what about the scale? if we switch everything to wind, won't the sheer volume of mining required for all those turbines create a permanent environmental scar that's just as bad as gas? doesn't the comparison change if you look at the total land and water use involved in both?",
